<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this subchapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0db91f3b-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s2144/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> $250,000 for fiscal year 2001; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0db91f3c-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s2144/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> such sums as may be necessary for each succeeding fiscal year.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id0db91f3d-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/380/s5">Pub. L. 106–380, § 5</ref>, <date date="2000-10-27">Oct. 27, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1449">114 Stat. 1449</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
